WEBVTT

00:06.136 --> 00:07.355
PREVIOUSLY ON
"PUSHING DAISIES"...

00:07.398 --> 00:09.096
Narrator:
YOUNG NED HAD A SPECIAL GIFT.

00:09.226 --> 00:12.142
HE COULD TOUCH DEAD THINGS
AND BRING THEM BACK TO LIFE.

00:12.186 --> 00:15.189
BUT HE COULD ONLY BRING THE DEAD
BACK TO LIFE FOR ONE MINUTE.

00:15.232 --> 00:18.061
ANY LONGER AND SOMEONE ELSE
HAD TO DIE.

00:18.105 --> 00:21.064
AND THERE WAS ONE MORE THING
HE HAD TO LEARN --

00:21.108 --> 00:22.370
FIRST TOUCH, LIFE.

00:22.413 --> 00:25.242
SECOND TOUCH,
DEAD AGAIN FOREVER.

00:25.286 --> 00:27.810
BUT AS YOUNG NED GREW
INTO THE PIE MAKER,

00:27.853 --> 00:30.073
THIS GIFT PROVED TO BE
MOST USEFUL

00:30.117 --> 00:32.858
IN THE UNTIMELY DEATH
OF HIS CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES.

00:32.902 --> 00:34.773
ARE YOU IN LOVE WITH HER?
YOU ONLY GOT A MINUTE.I KNOW.

00:34.817 --> 00:36.775
60 SECONDS.I KNOW.

00:36.819 --> 00:38.603
WHAT IF YOU
DIDN'T HAVE TO BE DEAD?

00:38.647 --> 00:41.041
YOU CAN'T TOUCH ME.SO A KISS IS
OUT OF THE QUESTION?

00:41.084 --> 00:43.956
Chuck:
YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS,
YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.741
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN,
THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

00:45.784 --> 00:47.221
AND THEN YOU COLLECT
THE REWARD?

00:47.264 --> 00:49.136
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.

00:51.877 --> 00:54.097
YOU SAVED ME!

00:54.141 --> 00:57.100
IT WAS A FRIENDLY EXPRESSION
OF INNOCENT GRATITUDE.

00:57.144 --> 00:58.101
[ LAUGHS ]

00:58.145 --> 00:59.276
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU?

00:59.320 --> 01:01.061
WHAT'S GOTTEN INTO YOU?

01:13.160 --> 01:16.293
Narrator:
AT THIS VERY MOMENT, AT
THE LONGBOROUGH SCHOOL FOR BOYS,

01:16.337 --> 01:20.950
YOUNG NED WAS 9 YEARS, 41 WEEKS,
14 HOURS, AND 3 MINUTES OLD

01:20.993 --> 01:23.387
AND EXHAUSTED...

01:23.431 --> 01:27.478
FOR, DESPITE THE ENDLESS WAKING
HOURS SPENT ASSURING HIMSELF

01:27.522 --> 01:29.611
THAT HIS HEART WAS ON THE MEND,

01:29.654 --> 01:33.397
NED DISCOVERED THE TRUTH
IN HIS SLEEP.

01:33.441 --> 01:35.617
SADLY, NOT A SINGLE NIGHT
HAD PASSED

01:35.660 --> 01:37.749
SINCE THE DEATH OF HIS MOTHER

01:37.793 --> 01:40.839
THAT HE DIDN'T DREAM
OF HER COMING BACK TO HIM.

01:47.107 --> 01:51.023
REALIZING HE COULDN'T
RUSH HIS HEART INTO HEALING,

01:51.067 --> 01:52.851
HE CONCOCTED A PLAN...

01:58.727 --> 02:03.384
...TO RECONNECT WITH HIS MOTHER
IN A WAY THAT ONLY HE COULD.

02:06.517 --> 02:09.303
FOR YOUNG NED WASN'T LIKE
THE OTHER CHILDREN

02:09.346 --> 02:11.827
OR THE OTHER ADULTS,
FOR THAT MATTER,

02:11.870 --> 02:15.004
WHICH, IN THIS CASE,
DELIGHTED HIM...

02:15.047 --> 02:16.962
BRIEFLY.

02:17.006 --> 02:20.531
ALTHOUGH YOUNG NED KNEW
HE COULDN'T TASTE THE PIE,

02:20.575 --> 02:24.970
LEST THE FRUIT ROT AGAIN,
HE DIDN'T CARE.

02:25.014 --> 02:29.410
THE MERE SMELL OF IT MADE HIM
FEEL, IF ONLY FOR AN HOUR,

02:29.453 --> 02:32.326
EXACTLY LIKE
HE WANTED TO FEEL --

02:32.369 --> 02:36.156
SAFE AND WARM AND LOVED --

02:36.199 --> 02:38.506
WHICH IS WHY HE BECAME...

02:38.549 --> 02:42.379
THE PIE MAKER...

02:42.423 --> 02:45.730
WHO, AT THIS VERY MOMENT,
WAS PLANTING FLOWERS

02:45.774 --> 02:49.038
TO MAKE CHUCK FEEL
AS SAFE AND WARM AND LOVED

02:49.081 --> 02:51.083
AS HE ONCE DID.

02:51.127 --> 02:52.781
SUE BEE.

02:52.824 --> 02:54.086
WHO BEE?

02:54.130 --> 02:55.479
I'M REFERRING
TO THE HONEY --

02:55.523 --> 02:56.872
THE STORE-BOUGHT KIND,

02:56.915 --> 02:59.353
THE KIND I WILL PURCHASE
BY THE GALLON FOR YOU.

02:59.396 --> 03:02.182
HONEY YOU DON'T WORK FOR
IS NEVER AS SWEET.

03:02.225 --> 03:03.705
OH, LOOK.

03:03.748 --> 03:05.228
THERE'S A FANTASTIC ROOFTOP

03:05.272 --> 03:06.795
FOR THE HONEY-HARVESTING
EXPANSION.

03:06.838 --> 03:08.710
LET'S NOT PLANT FLOWERS
WAY OVER THERE.

03:08.753 --> 03:10.929
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHICH BUILDING.

03:10.973 --> 03:12.409
I KNOW IT'S NOT THIS ONE.

03:12.453 --> 03:15.064
AND IN THE INTEREST OF
OPERATION URBAN HONEY PIONEER,

03:15.107 --> 03:17.545
I THINK WE SHOULD KEEP
THE OPERATION CONTAINED.

03:17.588 --> 03:19.024
COMFORTABLY CONTAINED.

03:19.068 --> 03:21.505
COMFORTABLE IN A GOOD WAY,
LIKE IT'S USUALLY USED.

03:21.549 --> 03:23.115
I'M CONCERNED FOR THE BEES.

03:23.159 --> 03:25.379
WE SHOULD KEEP THE FLOWERS CLOSE
SO THEY WILL FEEL SAFE.

03:25.422 --> 03:27.729
ACTUALLY, BEES HAVE
AN INCREDIBLE SENSE OF SMELL.

03:27.772 --> 03:30.166
SO IF WE KEEP DOING OUR JOB
AND PLANTING THE FLOWERS,

03:30.210 --> 03:32.081
THE BEES WILL DO THEIRS
AND FIND THEM.

03:32.124 --> 03:34.083
WHY DO WE NEED
SO MUCH HONEY, ANYWAY?

03:34.126 --> 03:35.911
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S A SURPRISE.

03:35.954 --> 03:37.956
"SURPRISE" HAS NEVER BEEN
A VERY GOOD WORD FOR ME.

03:38.000 --> 03:39.131
WELL,
YOU'LL LIKE THIS ONE.

03:39.175 --> 03:40.698
AND JUST SO YOU KNOW,

03:40.742 --> 03:42.396
THE HONEYBEE HAS TO VISIT
HUNDREDS OF BLOSSOMS

03:42.439 --> 03:44.789
BEFORE IT HAS ENOUGH NECTAR
TO TAKE BACK TO THE HIVE,

03:44.833 --> 03:48.271
SO THE MORE FLOWERS,
THE MERRIER THE BEES.

03:48.315 --> 03:51.100
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:51.143 --> 03:53.755
Narrator:
A BROKENHEARTED OLIVE SNOOK

03:53.798 --> 03:57.280
FOUND HERSELF NAVIGATING
A MINEFIELD OF HER OWN MAKING.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.499
OH!OH!

03:58.542 --> 04:00.196
THIS IS WHAT IT IS,
ISN'T IT?

04:00.240 --> 04:03.286
UNLESS THAT'S NOT A ROLLING PIN
UNDER YOUR APRON.

04:06.637 --> 04:08.291
SORRY.

04:08.335 --> 04:10.162
OH! [ LAUGHS NERVOUSLY ]
ISN'T IT GREAT WE CAN JOKE?

04:10.206 --> 04:12.295
NOW THAT WE KNOW THERE'S
NOTHING GOING ON BETWEEN
US AND NEVER WAS,

04:12.339 --> 04:13.644
IT CAN BE FUNNY.

04:13.688 --> 04:15.385
OH, YEAH!

04:15.429 --> 04:17.300
I BET THIS SORT OF THING
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME
BETWEEN ADULTS.

04:17.344 --> 04:18.606
MIXED ROMANTIC MESSAGES.

04:18.649 --> 04:19.824
IN NO TIME,
WE'LL BE LOOKING BACK

04:19.868 --> 04:21.086
AND LAUGHING
TILL WE WET THE RUG...

04:21.130 --> 04:22.740
WHICH WE'LL THEN
WANT TO SHAMPOO.

04:22.784 --> 04:24.307
A COUPLE TIMES,
POSSIBLY THREE,

04:24.351 --> 04:26.091
DEPENDING ON
WHAT WE'VE BEEN DRINKING.

04:26.135 --> 04:27.571
YEAH.
[ CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY ]

04:27.615 --> 04:28.746
WHOA!OH!

04:28.790 --> 04:31.314
MAYBE I SHOULD WEAR
A BELL.

04:31.358 --> 04:33.577
ACTUALLY --I'M NOT WEARING A BELL.

04:33.621 --> 04:35.231
Narrator:
CHUCK CONTINUED

04:35.275 --> 04:38.321
TO KEEP THE SECRET INGREDIENT
OF HER PIES SECRET.

04:38.365 --> 04:41.237
NOT EVEN OLIVE SNOOK KNEW
THE BAKED GOODS SHE DELIVERED

04:41.281 --> 04:44.327
CONTAINED HOMEOPATHIC
MOOD ENHANCERS

04:44.371 --> 04:46.068
MEANT TO PRY CHUCK'S AUNTS
OUT OF THEIR FUNK.

04:46.111 --> 04:49.898
SO, HAVE THEY BEEN
IN A GOOD MOOD? MY AUNTS?

04:49.941 --> 04:52.074
NO, THAT'S PLURAL,
AND NOT ALL OF THEM GOOD.

04:52.117 --> 04:54.250
OKAY. MAYBE IT'S TIME
TO GO TO PHASE TWO.

04:54.294 --> 04:56.905
HAVE WE BEEN IN PHASE ONE
THIS WHOLE TIME?
MM-HMM.

04:56.948 --> 04:58.559
HOW MANY PHASES
ARE THERE?

04:58.602 --> 05:00.387
FOUR THAT I KNOW OF,
BUT MAYBE FIVE.

05:00.430 --> 05:02.214
RIGHT NOW,
WE'RE AT PHASE TWO,

05:02.258 --> 05:04.391
WHICH MEANS WE NEED TO
GET THEM BACK IN THE WATER.

05:04.434 --> 05:05.566
IT'S LIKE OXYGEN FOR THEM.

05:05.609 --> 05:07.002
BECAUSE
THEY'RE FORMER MERMAIDS.

05:07.045 --> 05:09.396
ONLY PROFESSIONALLY,
NOT MYTHOLOGICALLY SPEAKING.

05:09.439 --> 05:11.267
OH, I KNOW ALL ABOUT
THEIR MERMAIDNESS.

05:11.311 --> 05:13.574
WHAT ARE THESE?
CUPCAKE PANS?

05:13.617 --> 05:14.923
SURPRISE.

05:14.966 --> 05:17.055
HUH?

05:17.099 --> 05:19.928
IT'S THE PIE HOLE,
NOT THE CUPCAKE HOLE.

05:19.971 --> 05:21.495
BUT IT'S NOT A CUPCAKE.
IT'S A CUP-PIE.

05:21.538 --> 05:22.974
A SINGLE-SERVE PIE
WITH HONEY --

05:23.018 --> 05:24.933
MY HONEY --
BAKED INTO THE CRUST.

05:24.976 --> 05:26.456
AND SINCE IT'S STILL A PIE,

05:26.500 --> 05:27.936
IT COULD BE SERVED IN
THE PIE HOLE, BY DEFINITION.

05:27.979 --> 05:29.633
I'M A PURIST.

05:29.677 --> 05:31.331
I LIKE THAT WE ONLY
SERVE TRADITIONAL PIES
IN THE PIE HOLE,

05:31.374 --> 05:33.245
NOT THESE HYBRIDS.

05:33.289 --> 05:35.900
YOU KNOW, YOU COULD DO
WITH LOOSENING UP A BIT.I DON'T DO LOOSE.

05:35.944 --> 05:37.249
I PREFER TIGHTLY WOUND.

05:37.293 --> 05:39.600
NOT SHAPELESS
WITH EXTRA ROOM FOR SURPRISES.

05:39.643 --> 05:41.384
I WAS A SURPRISE.

05:41.428 --> 05:44.387
YOU MADE ROOM FOR ME.
SOME.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.867
YEAH, I MADE ROOM.

05:45.910 --> 05:48.565
A WHOLE ROOFTOP FULL OF ROOM
FOR YOU AND YOUR BEES.

05:48.609 --> 05:50.524
I KNOW, AND I LOVE IT.

05:50.567 --> 05:52.874
I'M NOT QUASIMODO
IN THE BELL TOWER.

05:52.917 --> 05:54.179
QUASIMODO WOULD HAVE BEEN
A LOT BETTER OFF

05:54.223 --> 05:55.442
IF HE STAYED
IN HIS BELL TOWER

05:55.485 --> 05:57.226
WHERE IT WAS SAFE
AND COMFORTABLE,

05:57.269 --> 05:58.706
AND HE HAD HIS BELL.

05:58.749 --> 06:00.447
I'M NOT SURE QUASIMODO
WOULD AGREE WITH THAT.

06:00.490 --> 06:02.797
QUASI WANTED ADVENTURE.
QUASI WANTED TO SEE THE WORLD.

06:02.840 --> 06:03.885
QUASI WANTED CUP-PIES.

06:05.234 --> 06:06.453
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

06:06.496 --> 06:08.977
Narrator:
PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR EMERSON COD

06:09.020 --> 06:12.154
WAS ENJOYING THE LATEST ISSUE
OF KNIT WITMAGAZINE,

06:12.197 --> 06:15.070
HIS LITERARY OUTLET
FOR KNITTING HUMOR,

06:15.113 --> 06:17.115
WHEN HE RECEIVED A PHONE CALL

06:17.159 --> 06:18.900
FROM THE MOTHER
OF ONE ANITA GRAY.

06:18.943 --> 06:20.641
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

06:20.684 --> 06:21.859
[ GROANS ]

06:21.903 --> 06:23.774
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

06:23.818 --> 06:25.559
ANITA GRAY --

06:25.602 --> 06:29.345
22 YEARS, 11 WEEKS, 2 DAYS,
9 HOURS, AND 33 MINUTES OLD --

06:29.389 --> 06:32.957
WAS TAKING A PRIVATE TUTORIAL
IN OLFACTORY SCIENCE

06:33.001 --> 06:36.308
WHEN SHE EXPERIENCED
AN EPIPHANY.

06:36.352 --> 06:38.528
AND THE EPIPHANY WAS
THAT HER INSTRUCTOR,

06:38.572 --> 06:41.705
NAPOLEON LeNEZ, WAS A GENIUS.

06:41.749 --> 06:43.098
IT WAS AN EPIPHANY

06:43.141 --> 06:45.709
NAPOLEON LeNEZ
HAD HIMSELF EXPERIENCED

06:45.753 --> 06:47.668
MANY, MANY YEARS EARLIER.

06:47.711 --> 06:52.063
HE SHOWED HER HOW OLFACTORY CUES
COULD TRIGGER MEMORIES,

06:52.107 --> 06:55.110
RELEASE FLOODS OF ENDORPHINS
AND PHEROMONES,

06:55.153 --> 06:58.418
AND CAUSE BIOLOGICAL
AND PSYCHOLOGICAL REACTIONS

06:58.461 --> 07:02.247
THAT DEEPLY IMPACTED THE WAY
PEOPLE BEHAVE AND FEEL.

07:03.335 --> 07:05.903
USING THE SMELL
OF UNFILTERED CIGARETTES

07:05.947 --> 07:08.297
TO EVOKE FOND MEMORIES
OF HER GRANDMOTHER,

07:08.340 --> 07:12.867
HE OPENED HER EYES AND HEART
THROUGH HER NOSE.

07:15.609 --> 07:19.917
SO SHE DEVOTED HER LIFE
TO HIS WORK.

07:19.961 --> 07:22.354
WITH HIS NEW APPRENTICE, ANITA,
BY HIS SIDE,

07:22.398 --> 07:24.269
LeNEZ CREATED A SELF-HELP GUIDE

07:24.313 --> 07:27.447
FOR THOSE WHO WISHED TO
NOT ONLY HARNESS THEIR PAST

07:27.490 --> 07:29.753
BUT TO INSPIRE
AND MOLD THEIR FUTURE

07:29.797 --> 07:31.712
VIA THE POWER OF SMELL.

07:31.755 --> 07:34.279
ANITA DIDN'T LIVE
TO SEE THE BOOK PUBLISHED.

07:34.323 --> 07:35.933
WHILE WORKING ALONE,

07:35.977 --> 07:40.895
SHE WAS KILLED BY A MYSTERIOUS
EXPLOSION IN LeNEZ'S LAB.

07:40.938 --> 07:44.115
EXACTLY WHAT CAUSED
THAT EXPLOSION

07:44.159 --> 07:48.293
SEEMED TO BE A QUESTION
ONLY ANITA GRAY COULD ANSWER.

07:48.337 --> 07:49.643
WHOA! WHOA.

07:49.686 --> 07:51.296
THAT IS PUNGENT.

07:51.340 --> 07:54.082
YEAH, PUNGENT LIKE FRIED CHICKEN
GRILLED ON A BED OF HAIR.

07:54.125 --> 07:56.650
WELL,
WHAT YOU WAITING ON?

07:56.693 --> 07:58.260
[ WATCH TICKING ]MNH.

08:00.305 --> 08:02.482
[ SNIFFS ]
WHO'S SMOKING?

08:02.525 --> 08:03.831
YOU.

08:03.874 --> 08:05.963
OH, HOW RUDE OF ME.
I'M DREADFULLY SORRY.

08:06.007 --> 08:07.791
THIS CAN'T BE GOOD
FOR YOUR LUNGS.

08:07.835 --> 08:10.751
ANITA, YOU HAVE
LESS THAN A MINUTE TO
IMPART ANY LAST WORDS.

08:10.794 --> 08:12.927
ON THE SUBJECT OF WHAT
CAUSED THAT EXPLOSION.

08:12.970 --> 08:15.233
"EXPLOSION"?
THAT'S WHAT THAT FLASH WAS.

08:15.277 --> 08:17.061
DO YOU REMEMBER ANYTHING
BEFORE THE FLASH?

08:17.105 --> 08:20.717
THE SMELL OF MY GRANDMA'S
UNFILTERED CIGARETTES.

08:20.761 --> 08:24.504
Narrator: UNFORTUNATELY,
ANITA'S DESIRE TO EXPERIENCE

08:24.547 --> 08:26.897
ANOTHER OLFACTORY-INDUCED MEMORY

08:26.941 --> 08:29.900
OF HER BELOVED GRANDMOTHER,
LONG DEAD FROM CANCER,

08:29.944 --> 08:31.598
LED HER TO SNEAK A LOOK

08:31.641 --> 08:35.166
AT THE ONE AND ONLY
ADVANCED COPY OF LeNEZ'S BOOK,

08:35.210 --> 08:38.126
A BOOK THAT WAS MEANT
FOR HIS NOSE ONLY.

08:38.169 --> 08:40.998
THIS WAS CLEARLY A CASE OF...

08:41.042 --> 08:43.000
DEATH BY
SCRATCH-AND-SNIFF?

08:43.044 --> 08:45.002
SO LeNEZ DIDN'T WANT YOU
LOOKING AT THAT BOOK?

08:45.046 --> 08:46.830
HE DIDN'T WANT ANYONE
LOOKING AT IT YET.

08:46.874 --> 08:49.833
OH, NO. WAS I BEING PUNISHED
FOR PEEKING? IS GOD MAD AT ME?

08:49.877 --> 08:52.140
NO. NO, GOD IS NOT
MAD AT YOU.

08:52.183 --> 08:53.837
[ Mumbling ] SOMEBODY'S
MAD AT SOMEBODY.

08:53.881 --> 08:55.622
SOMEBODY'S MAD
AT NAPOLEON LeNEZ.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.493
THAT DAMN BOOK
WAS BOOBY-TRAPPED.

08:57.537 --> 08:59.277
[ WATCH BEEPS ]OH, 5 SECONDS.

08:59.321 --> 09:01.323
AM I GONNA SEE
MY GRANDMA NOW?AS FAR AS YOU KNOW.

09:01.366 --> 09:03.064
THAT'S A YES.

09:03.107 --> 09:04.587
DEATH BY
SCRATCH-AND-SNIFF --

09:04.631 --> 09:06.023
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED

09:06.067 --> 09:07.982
TO PEOPLE SHOOTING
EACH OTHER WITH GUNS?

09:12.769 --> 09:14.597
Narrator: ANXIOUS TO SNIFF OUT
MORE INFORMATION,

09:14.641 --> 09:16.991
OUR HEROES SOUGHT OUT
NAPOLEON LeNEZ,

09:17.034 --> 09:20.821
SCRATCH-AND-SNIFF AUTHOR,
IN HIS SUITE ABOVE THE CITY

09:20.864 --> 09:23.867
AND IMMEDIATELY FOUND THEMSELVES
IN AN ALARMING SITUATION.

09:23.911 --> 09:25.216
[ ALARM BLARES ]

09:25.260 --> 09:26.783
DO NOT BE ALARMED
BY THIS SITUATION.

09:26.827 --> 09:29.394
[ AIR BLOWING ]HEY!

09:29.438 --> 09:31.092
HEY!

09:35.444 --> 09:37.228
YOU BETTER OPEN UP
THIS DOOR!

09:42.233 --> 09:46.107
[ RUMBLING ]

09:47.325 --> 09:49.806
[ CLICKS, DOOR OPENS ]

09:54.506 --> 09:57.422
PLEASE EXCUSE
MY DECONTAMINATION PROCEDURE.

09:57.466 --> 09:59.207
MY NASAL GLANDS ARE
EXTREMELY DELICATE.

09:59.250 --> 10:00.687
NAPOLEON LeNEZ?

10:00.730 --> 10:01.905
FELICITATIONS.

10:01.949 --> 10:03.428
FELICI-WHAT?

10:03.472 --> 10:05.300
UM, WE'RE HERE
ABOUT YOUR ASSISTANT --

10:05.343 --> 10:08.999
DON'T SPEAK.
A SMELL TELLS SO MUCH MORE.

10:11.045 --> 10:14.309
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

10:15.440 --> 10:19.053
[ EXHALES SOFTLY ]
CIGARS, AFTERSHAVE,

10:19.096 --> 10:22.534
ANTACIDS, CASH...
AND YARN.

10:22.578 --> 10:24.493
YOU'RE
A KNITTING DETECTIVE.

10:24.536 --> 10:25.494
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:25.537 --> 10:26.843
AND YOU.

10:30.542 --> 10:33.937
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

10:33.981 --> 10:37.593
[ EXHALES SOFTLY ]
FLOUR, FRUIT,

10:37.637 --> 10:41.945
AND A SUBTLE WAFT OF MUSKY
PHEROMONES TRIGGERED BY --

10:41.989 --> 10:43.468
MNH-MNH!

10:43.512 --> 10:44.513
[ CHUCKLING ]

10:44.556 --> 10:47.472
YOU...

10:47.516 --> 10:51.738
THE GIRL SMELLING OF HONEY
AND...[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

10:51.781 --> 10:53.304
DEATH.

10:55.350 --> 10:57.308
WHICH DOESN'T SURPRISE ME,

10:57.352 --> 10:59.876
AS THE ANIMALIC-CHARGED
MOLECULES USED IN YOUR PERFUME

10:59.920 --> 11:02.096
ARE ALSO FOUND IN
DECOMPOSING BODIES AND FECES.

11:02.139 --> 11:03.663
OH, I'M NOT WEARING
ANY PERFUME.

11:03.706 --> 11:04.751
[ COUGHS ]

11:04.794 --> 11:07.449
I'M NOT WEARING
JUST ANY PERFUME.

11:07.492 --> 11:10.582
PRECISELY MY POINT.
WHY SETTLE FOR LESS?

11:10.626 --> 11:13.455
IN ALL ASPECTS OF LIFE,
WE STRIVE FOR PERFECTION.

11:13.498 --> 11:16.284
WHY NOT APPLY THOSE PRINCIPLES
TO WHAT WE SMELL?

11:16.327 --> 11:17.894
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
YEAH, YEAH.

11:17.938 --> 11:19.504
LeNEZ, LOOK, WE'RE HERE
ABOUT THAT SCRATCH-AND-SNIFF.

11:19.548 --> 11:20.984
YOUR BOOK WAS A BOMB.

11:21.028 --> 11:24.814
WHO ARE YOUTO CRITICIZE
MY LIFE'S WORK?

11:24.858 --> 11:27.730
YOUR BOOK WAS A BOMB.

11:27.774 --> 11:29.906
IT EXPLODED.

11:29.950 --> 11:32.474
Narrator: THE KILLER HAD USED
A UNIQUE EXPLOSIVE

11:32.517 --> 11:34.998
ON LeNEZ'S ADVANCED COPY
OF THE BOOK,

11:35.042 --> 11:37.218
A CHEMICAL MIXED
WITH AN OXIDIZING AGENT

11:37.261 --> 11:39.481
TO CREATE
A FIERY CHAIN REACTION.

11:39.524 --> 11:40.961
[ EXPLOSION ]

11:41.004 --> 11:42.876
ARE THEY STILL GONNA
PUBLISH YOUR BOOK?

11:42.919 --> 11:45.574
ANITA WOULD HAVE
WANTED IT THAT WAY,

11:45.617 --> 11:47.619
ALTHOUGH I'M SURE
SHE WOULD HAVE PREFERRED

11:47.663 --> 11:49.099
A VERSION WHERE SHE LIVED.

11:49.143 --> 11:52.233
STILL, SHE WAS THRILLED
WHEN MY PUBLISHER BUMPED UP

11:52.276 --> 11:53.800
THE RELEASE DATE
OF "SMELL OF SUCCESS."

11:53.843 --> 11:55.671
WHEN DID THEY BUMP UP
YOUR "SMELL"?

11:55.715 --> 11:57.194
TWO WEEKS AGO.

11:57.238 --> 11:58.630
FOLLOW YOUR NOSE, MR. COD,

11:58.674 --> 12:01.198
AND IT WILL LEAD YOU
TO THIS DEVIANT'S DOORSTEP.

12:01.242 --> 12:03.200
WHEN WE HARNESS
THE POWER OF SMELL,

12:03.244 --> 12:06.726
WE BECOME BLOODHOUNDS
OF OUR OWN DESIRES.

12:06.769 --> 12:10.642
SMELL IT,
CRAVE IT, OWN IT.

12:13.297 --> 12:17.475
I CAN WEAR THEM?
YOU MEAN IT? ON MY FEET?

12:17.519 --> 12:19.390
UNLESS YOU'RE CURSED
WITH A SIXTH TOE.

12:20.261 --> 12:21.871
YOU'RE NOT, ARE YOU?

12:21.915 --> 12:24.134
NO, NO.
FIVE FINGERS, FIVE TOES.

12:24.178 --> 12:26.136
US SNOOKS ARE BORING
THAT WAY.

12:26.180 --> 12:28.225
I HAD A COUSIN
WITH A THIRD NIPPLE.

12:28.269 --> 12:30.227
HE'D LET YOU SEE IT
FOR A DOLLAR.

12:30.271 --> 12:31.794
HOW FASCINATING.

12:31.838 --> 12:34.144
AND A BARGAIN, TOO.

12:34.188 --> 12:35.450
THIS IS A DREAM
COME TRUE.

12:35.493 --> 12:37.844
AAH! AAH! AAH!

12:37.887 --> 12:39.149
[ LAUGHTER ]

12:39.193 --> 12:40.890
OH, I HOPE THIS DOESN'T
FREAK YOU OUT,

12:40.934 --> 12:44.589
BUT I USED TO BE A BIG DARLING
MERMAID DARLINGS ENTHUSIAST.

12:44.633 --> 12:46.635
I HAD THE TAIL
AND THE CLAMSHELL BRA.

12:46.678 --> 12:48.855
OH!
JUST LIKE THIS ONE.

12:48.898 --> 12:51.031
DID YOU SHOW THAT OFF
FOR A DOLLAR?

12:51.074 --> 12:53.120
OH, I BET YOU MISS
YOUR FANS.

12:53.163 --> 12:54.599
I KNOW I WOULD --

12:54.643 --> 12:56.950
ALL THE ADORATION,
ALL THE LOVE.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.473
DOESN'T
ALL THIS PARAPHERNALIA

12:58.516 --> 13:00.257
MAKE YOU WANT TO GET
BACK IN THE POOL?

13:00.301 --> 13:01.519
HAVE NO REASON TO.

13:01.563 --> 13:04.653
UM, WE CANCELLED
OUR COMEBACK TOUR.

13:04.696 --> 13:06.655
BUT LOOK AT
ALL THIS STUFF.

13:06.698 --> 13:10.311
IMAGINE THE MONEY YOU'LL MAKE
FROM MERCHANDISING ALONE.

13:10.354 --> 13:12.792
OH. WHAT'S THIS?

13:12.835 --> 13:14.924
THAT BELONGED
TO CHARLOTTE.

13:14.968 --> 13:16.578
IT WAS HER MOTHER'S.

13:18.014 --> 13:20.756
WHATEVER HAPPENED
TO CHARLOTTE'S MOTHER?

13:20.800 --> 13:22.323
SHE DIED.

13:22.366 --> 13:25.979
Narrator: AND WITH THAT,
LILY WENT TO HER DARK PLACE.

13:26.022 --> 13:28.459
YOU WANT IT?
TAKE IT.

13:28.503 --> 13:32.333
I DON'T CARE IF I EVER GET
IN THE WATER AGAIN.

13:32.376 --> 13:35.162
FOR THE LOVE OF
KUKLA, FRAN, AND OLLIE,

13:35.205 --> 13:38.121
RENT THE GIRL A HAND TRUCK
AND GET THIS CRAP OUT OF HERE.

13:38.165 --> 13:40.428
I NEED A PIECE OF PIE.

13:43.735 --> 13:46.695
Ned: DO YOU REALLY THINK
PEOPLE CAN CHANGE THEIR LIVES

13:46.738 --> 13:48.523
BY SMELLING
THE RIGHT SMELL?

13:48.566 --> 13:50.568
IF SO, I'M GONNA GET ME
SOME CASH POTPOURRI.

13:50.612 --> 13:52.266
I TALKED TO THAT PUBLISHER.

13:52.309 --> 13:54.703
LeNEZ'S BOOK WASBUMPED UP
THE RELEASE SCHEDULE

13:54.746 --> 13:56.139
PRIOR
TO ANITA GRAY'S MURDER.

13:56.183 --> 13:57.662
SO...

13:57.706 --> 13:59.360
SO IF LeNEZ'S BOOK GOT
MOVED UP THE SCHEDULE,

13:59.403 --> 14:01.101
SOMEBODY ELSE'S BOOK
GOT MOVED OFF.

14:01.144 --> 14:03.538
FIND THE BOOK THAT WAS
FORMERLY ON THIS SCHEDULE

14:03.581 --> 14:05.235
THAT IS NO LONGER
ON THIS SCHEDULE,

14:05.279 --> 14:07.150
AND YOU'LL FIND AN ANGRY AUTHOR
WITH A MOTIVE TO KILL.

14:07.194 --> 14:08.630
LOOK.

14:08.673 --> 14:10.327
A SLICE OF PIE IS TOO MUCH
FOR SOME CUSTOMERS.

14:10.371 --> 14:12.025
A CUP-PIE
WOULD BE PERFECT.

14:12.068 --> 14:13.678
SEE THAT? SEE WHAT
YOU JUST DID JUST NOW?

14:13.722 --> 14:15.724
YOU INTERRUPTED OUR CONVERSATION
WITH YOUR CUP-PIE CHATTER

14:15.767 --> 14:17.378
WHEN I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT A CUP-PIE IS,

14:17.421 --> 14:19.380
WHICH MEANS I DON'T GIVE
A DAMN WHAT A CUP-PIE IS.

14:19.423 --> 14:20.642
OH, I'M SORRY.

14:20.685 --> 14:22.035
A CUP-PIE
IS A SINGLE-SERVE PIE

14:22.078 --> 14:23.384
WITH A HONEY-BAKED CRUST.

14:23.427 --> 14:24.907
DOESN'T THAT SOUND GOOD?

14:24.951 --> 14:27.040
SOUNDS DELICIOUS,
BUT WE DON'T SERVE THEM HERE.

14:27.083 --> 14:29.346
AM I SERIOUSLY
THE FIRST PERSON

14:29.390 --> 14:31.914
TO QUESTION YOUR AVERSION
TO CHANGE?

14:31.958 --> 14:34.221
WHAT ABOUT
YOUR EX-GIRLFRIENDS?

14:34.264 --> 14:36.005
EMERSON DOESN'T WANT TO HEAR
ABOUT ANY OF THIS.

14:36.049 --> 14:39.139
I MUST ADMIT,
I AMCURIOUS.

14:40.270 --> 14:41.924
HELL, BEFORE DEAD GIRL
CAME ALONG,

14:41.968 --> 14:44.144
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT YOU LIKED,
OR IF YOU LIKED,

14:44.187 --> 14:45.928
OR IF YOU HAD ANYTHING
TO LIKE WITH.

14:45.972 --> 14:48.017
FOR ALL I KNOW, YOU COULD HAVE
BEEN ONE OF THOSE PEOPLE

14:48.061 --> 14:50.411
WHO WAS BORN WITH BOTH
BUT DIDN'T USE EITHER.

14:50.454 --> 14:51.891
I'VE HAD GIRLFRIENDS,

14:51.934 --> 14:53.893
BUT THERE WERE ALWAYS
EXTRANEOUS FACTORS.

14:53.936 --> 14:55.503
WHAT KIND OF EXTRANEOUS
FACTORS?
WHAT KIND OF
EXTRANEOUS FACTORS?

14:55.546 --> 14:59.724
YOU KNOW, WE, UM...
GREW APART

14:59.768 --> 15:02.379
AND...LOST INTEREST,

15:02.423 --> 15:04.904
HAD INTIMATE RELATIONS
ON A BEARSKIN RUG.

15:04.947 --> 15:07.254
OH, NO, DID IT...

15:07.297 --> 15:08.995
IT DID ENOUGH
TO BE UPSETTING.

15:09.038 --> 15:11.040
COME ON.

15:11.084 --> 15:12.259
W-WHAT'S ALL THIS?

15:12.302 --> 15:13.869
GIRL BUSINESS.
BONDING.

15:15.653 --> 15:17.090
HUH?

15:17.133 --> 15:19.919
PHASE TWO HAS EXPERIENCED
A HICCUP.

15:19.962 --> 15:21.790
THE KIND OF HICCUP
THAT GOES AWAY

15:21.833 --> 15:23.792
IF YOU HAVE A GLASS OF WATER
OR HOLD YOUR BREATH?

15:23.835 --> 15:26.969
NO, THE KIND OF HICCUP
THAT KEEPS YOU UP FOR DAYS
ON END TILL YOU GO CRAZY

15:27.013 --> 15:29.450
AND YOU GIVE AWAY ALL
YOUR CHERISHED MERMAID MEMENTOS

15:29.493 --> 15:31.452
AND REFUSE TO GET
BACK IN THE POOL AGAIN.

15:31.495 --> 15:34.107
OH, NO. HAVE THEY BEEN
EATING THEIR PIE?

15:34.150 --> 15:35.978
CHUCK, A SLICE OF PIE CAN'T
SOLVE ALL THEIR PROBLEMS.

15:36.022 --> 15:37.762
WE JUST NEED TO GIVE THEM
STRONGER PIE

15:37.806 --> 15:39.677
AND GIVE THEM A LITTLE
PUSH...INTO THE WATER.

15:39.721 --> 15:42.245
BUT I HAVE BEEN PUSHING.YOU NEED TO PUSH HARDER.

15:42.289 --> 15:45.945
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER FEARED
CHUCK AND OLIVE BONDING

15:45.988 --> 15:50.427
WAS LIKE A CHEMICAL ACCELERANT
BONDING WITH AN OXIDIZING AGENT.

15:50.471 --> 15:53.822
AN EXPLOSION
WAS BOUND TO POP UP.

15:53.865 --> 15:54.954
OOH, POP-UPS!

15:54.997 --> 15:56.216
WHAT?

15:56.259 --> 15:58.827
POP-UP BOOKS!
I LOVEPOP-UP BOOKS.

15:58.870 --> 16:02.004
AND IF THE SACRED CASH COW
THAT I WORSHIP

16:02.048 --> 16:03.745
IS MOOING DOWN ON US...

16:03.788 --> 16:07.140
OUR KILLER
LIKES POP-UPS, TOO.

16:07.183 --> 16:08.663
[ CHUCKLING ]

16:08.706 --> 16:10.621
I LOVE POP-UP BOOKS.

16:12.362 --> 16:14.669
Narrator: EMERSON AND NED

16:14.712 --> 16:17.063
PURSUED PINNING DOWN
THE POP-UP AUTHOR.

16:17.106 --> 16:19.021
DO THAT ONE.

16:19.065 --> 16:21.241
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:21.284 --> 16:25.114
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
ARE YOU, UH, CHAS SPIELMAN,
AUTHOR OF "POP-UP PIN-UP"?

16:25.158 --> 16:26.333
THAT'S ME.

16:26.376 --> 16:28.161
ARE YOU HERE
FOR A SNEAK PEEK,

16:28.204 --> 16:30.424
OR SHOULD I SAY PEEP,
OF MY LATEST BOOK?

16:30.467 --> 16:33.601
I HEARD
THIS BOOK WAS CANCELED.

16:33.644 --> 16:37.344
ONLY TEMPORARILY.
I'M STILL WORKING ON THAT.

16:37.387 --> 16:41.174
THIS DON'T LOOK LIKE NO
POP-UP BOOK I HAD AS A CHILD.

16:41.217 --> 16:42.784
POP-UPS AREN'T
JUST FOR CHILDREN.

16:42.827 --> 16:45.830
MY POP-UPS ARE DESIGNED
FOR THEIR ORIGINAL AUDIENCE.

16:45.874 --> 16:47.006
PERVERTS?

16:47.049 --> 16:50.009
MATURE CONNOISSEURS
OF ART.

16:50.052 --> 16:53.186
Emerson: OR HOMICIDAL MANIACS
WITH RUDIMENTARY READING SKILLS.

16:53.229 --> 16:55.101
"THE NEW PATRIOT'S
POP-UP BOOK --

16:55.144 --> 16:57.059
"A THREE-DIMENSIONAL
INSTRUCTIONAL

16:57.103 --> 16:58.756
"TELLING YOU EVERYTHING
YOU WANTED TO KNOW

16:58.800 --> 17:03.196
ABOUT BUILDING BOMBS
OF ALL SHAPES AND SIZES."

17:03.239 --> 17:06.025
POP-UP PALACE APPEALS
TO AN UNUSUAL DEMOGRAPHIC.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.374
ANY INSTRUCTIONS IN HERE

17:07.417 --> 17:09.506
ON HOW TO BUILD
A SCRATCH-AND-SNIFF BOMB?

17:09.550 --> 17:12.335
IS THIS ABOUT THE ATTEMPT
ON NAPOLEON LeNEZ?

17:12.379 --> 17:15.817
WORD TRAVELS FAST
IN LITERARY CIRCLES.

17:15.860 --> 17:18.211
WELL, HIS BOOK DID BUMP "POP-UP
PIN-UP" OFF THE SCHEDULE.

17:18.254 --> 17:20.517
SEEMS LIKE A GOOD-ENOUGH MOTIVE
TO BLOW SOMEBODY UP.

17:20.561 --> 17:22.084
AND CLEARLY,
YOU HAVE THE MEANS.

17:22.128 --> 17:25.392
HMM.WHO WOULD PUBLISH A BOOK
ON HOW TO KILL SOMEBODY,

17:25.435 --> 17:28.221
THEN KILL SOMEBODY
THEY KNEW

17:28.264 --> 17:30.484
USING A METHOD THEY PUBLISHED
IN THE BOOK?

17:30.527 --> 17:31.311
OOH.

17:31.354 --> 17:32.921
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

17:32.964 --> 17:35.097
YEAH, WELL, I'M KEEPING
THIS BOOK AS EVIDENCE.

17:35.141 --> 17:36.533
MM-HMM.

17:36.577 --> 17:37.578
OOH.

17:37.621 --> 17:39.623
AND THESE, TOO.

17:47.979 --> 17:50.373
SO, YOU DIDN'T WANT
LeNEZ DEAD?

17:50.417 --> 17:52.419
I MAY BE PETTY,
BUT I'M NOT THATPETTY.

17:52.462 --> 17:54.464
BESIDES, THE PUBLISHER
MOVED LeNEZ'S BOOK

17:54.508 --> 17:58.164
FROM A PRIME HOLIDAY SPOT
TO NO-MAN'S-LAND.

17:58.207 --> 18:01.689
IF YOU ASK ME, HIS BOOK
WASN'T BUMPED, IT WAS DUMPED.

18:03.647 --> 18:04.474
HUH.

18:06.041 --> 18:09.131
OH, IT SMELLS LIKE FAMILY HOUR
AT THE PUBLIC POOL.

18:09.175 --> 18:11.394
OH, NO.
THAT'S NOT THE PIE.

18:11.438 --> 18:13.135
IT'S CHLORINE TABLETS.

18:13.179 --> 18:15.877
AUNT LILY USED TO SAY IT
SMELLS LIKE BOTTLED SUNSHINE.

18:15.920 --> 18:18.140
WELL, IF IT CAME IN A BOTTLE,
AUNT LILY WOULD LIKE IT.

18:18.184 --> 18:20.708
SEE, I'VE BEEN READING THIS
REALLY GOOD SELF-HELP BOOK.

18:20.751 --> 18:22.188
IT'S ABOUT
THE POWER OF SMELL.

18:22.231 --> 18:24.668
I THOUGHT WE'D TRY IT --
SEE WHAT HAPPENS

18:24.712 --> 18:27.976
WHEN YOU COMBINE PIE HAPPINESS
WITH THE HAPPINESS OF CHLORINE.

18:28.019 --> 18:30.457
[ CLATTERING, BUBBLING ]

18:30.500 --> 18:33.808
YOU KNOW, I READ
A SELF-HELP BOOK ONCE --

18:33.851 --> 18:35.331
"SAMSONIZED --

18:35.375 --> 18:37.812
HOW TO GROW YOUR HAIR TO BECOME
A MORE POWERFUL YOU."

18:37.855 --> 18:39.422
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:39.466 --> 18:41.946
TWO WEEKS LATER, AND I WAS
BALD AS A BABY'S BEHIND.

18:41.990 --> 18:44.906
LOOKS LIKE I'M NOT
THE ONLY ONE WHO READ IT.

18:44.949 --> 18:47.822
WHAT'S THE HAPS, PAPS?
ANY LUCK ON THE CASE?

18:47.865 --> 18:50.085
FIRST OF ALL,
I AIN'T YOUR PAPS.

18:50.129 --> 18:52.174
"PAPS" HAS
A LADY CONNOTATION.

18:52.218 --> 18:55.917
AND SECOND OF ALL, THIS AIN'T
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

18:55.960 --> 18:58.311
[ GURGLING ]OH, YUCK.

18:58.354 --> 19:01.444
THERE'S SOMETHING --
SOMETHING STUCK IN THERE.

19:05.231 --> 19:11.672
[ RATTLING, GURGLING ]

19:11.715 --> 19:12.673
OH!

19:12.716 --> 19:14.501
OHH! OHH!
OOH!

19:14.544 --> 19:16.503
UGH!

19:16.546 --> 19:18.418
OH, NO, THEY DIDN'T.

19:18.461 --> 19:20.376
Narrator: THE INTENT
OF THE WARNING WAS OBVIOUS.

19:20.420 --> 19:22.117
Olive:
"U CAN'T SAVE LeNEZ"?

19:22.161 --> 19:25.381
Narrator:
SOMEONE WANTED TO MAKE A STINK.

19:30.821 --> 19:32.432
OOH!UGH!

19:32.475 --> 19:34.564
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

19:34.608 --> 19:37.611
DECAY...

19:37.654 --> 19:38.916
A TINGE OF RUSTED IRON --

19:38.960 --> 19:43.007
HARSH BUT SPIKY,
WITH A SULFURIC EDGE.

19:43.051 --> 19:46.141
THIS LOATHSOME OMEN CAME UP
FROM THE SEWER,

19:46.185 --> 19:49.797
WHICH MEANS IT COULD HAVE
ONLY COME FROM ONE MAN --

19:49.840 --> 19:51.755
OSCAR VIBENIUS.

19:51.799 --> 19:54.889
Narrator: OSCAR VIBENIUS
AND NAPOLEON LeNEZ

19:54.932 --> 19:57.674
WERE LAB PARTNERS
AND THE BEST OF FRIENDS,

19:57.718 --> 20:01.287
UNTIL THEIR DIVERGENT OLFACTION
THEORIES TORE THEM APART.

20:01.330 --> 20:03.767
OSCAR FAVORED THE WILD,
UNFETTERED SMELLS

20:03.811 --> 20:05.073
OF THE NATURAL WORLD,

20:05.116 --> 20:06.553
BELIEVING THAT PEOPLE

20:06.596 --> 20:08.859
COULDN'T APPRECIATE
THE GOOD SMELLS IN LIFE

20:08.903 --> 20:10.470
WITHOUT SMELLING THE BAD.

20:10.513 --> 20:12.689
LeNEZ BELIEVED
THAT BECAUSE SMELL

20:12.733 --> 20:15.257
HAS A POWERFUL EFFECT
ON HUMAN BEHAVIOR,

20:15.301 --> 20:17.477
HUMANS SHOULD
SURROUND THEMSELVES

20:17.520 --> 20:20.262
WITH ONLY GOOD,
CAREFULLY CONTROLLED ODORS.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.438
OVER TIME, THEIR RIVALRY GREW

20:22.482 --> 20:25.528
UNTIL NEITHER MAN
COULD STAND THE OTHER.

20:25.572 --> 20:29.184
EACH RETREATED TO THE WORLDS
THEY FOUND MOST COMFORTABLE --

20:29.228 --> 20:32.448
ONE ABOVEGROUND...

20:32.492 --> 20:36.278
[ WATER DRIPPING ]AND ONE BELOW.

20:36.322 --> 20:38.324
THERE WAS REALLY
NOTHING I COULD DO.

20:38.367 --> 20:40.369
IT'S SAD,
BUT OSCAR WOULD DO ANYTHING

20:40.413 --> 20:42.763
TO PREVENT MY THEORIES
FROM BEING PUBLISHED.

20:42.806 --> 20:45.505
[ Nasally ] DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHERE HE COULD BE?

20:45.548 --> 20:47.333
THERE WERE RUMORS.

20:47.376 --> 20:50.205
SOME CLAIM
THAT HE COMMITTED SUICIDE.

20:50.249 --> 20:51.424
OTHERS WERE CONVINCED

20:51.467 --> 20:53.295
THAT HE ENDED UP
IN A MENTAL INSTITUTION,

20:53.339 --> 20:55.079
ONLY TO BE PUT
BACK ON THE STREET

20:55.123 --> 20:56.951
BY THE REAGAN ADMINISTRATION.

20:56.994 --> 21:00.171
I HEARD TALES OF OSCAR
ROAMING THE SEWERS,

21:00.215 --> 21:01.434
HAUNTING THEM,

21:01.477 --> 21:06.090
A SOURED HUSK
OF WHO HE ONCE WAS.

21:08.658 --> 21:11.226
BUT THEN SOMEONE RECENTLY
TOLD ME HE WORKED FOR THE DWP,

21:11.270 --> 21:13.881
SO THAT MIGHT EXPLAIN WHERE
SOME OF THOSE RUMORS CAME FROM.

21:13.924 --> 21:16.057
OH!

21:16.100 --> 21:20.627
LOOK CAREFULLY, LADIES.
THIS...IS YOUR FUTURE.

21:20.670 --> 21:22.237
IS IT VODKA?

21:22.281 --> 21:24.152
WATER.

21:24.195 --> 21:27.895
HMM.
AS IN RUSSIAN FOR VODKA?

21:27.938 --> 21:31.246
AS IN ENGLISH FOR H2O.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.683
Vivian: LILY DOESN'T BELIEVE
IN WATER ANYMORE.

21:33.727 --> 21:36.425
SHE THINKS IT'S A WASTE
OF A PERFECTLY GOOD TUMBLER.

21:36.469 --> 21:38.514
HMM.

21:41.430 --> 21:43.258
HOW ABOUT NOW?

21:43.302 --> 21:45.129
CHLORINE.

21:45.173 --> 21:48.742
LILY USED TO SAY
IT REMINDED HER
OF BOTTLED SUNSHINE.

21:50.134 --> 21:53.573
NOW IT REMINDS ME OF CHILDREN
WITHOUT BLADDER CONTROL.

21:53.616 --> 21:55.183
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

22:00.536 --> 22:04.714
WHY, LILY...
IS THAT A SMILE?

22:14.637 --> 22:16.073
[ BURPS ]

22:17.423 --> 22:18.946
JUST GAS.

22:18.989 --> 22:20.687
Narrator:
SO, SHE SWALLOWED HER HAPPINESS

22:20.730 --> 22:24.299
AND RETREATED TO THE SAFETY
OF HER USUAL DESPONDENCY.

22:24.343 --> 22:25.996
AS LILY'S GAS PASSED,

22:26.040 --> 22:28.782
OUR DETERMINED HEROES
FOLLOWED THE TUBE SOCK

22:28.825 --> 22:30.958
TO ITS OWN FOUL ORIGIN.

22:31.001 --> 22:32.351
OSCAR VIBENIUS!

22:32.394 --> 22:34.309
WE'RE REALLY WALKING AROUND
DOWN HERE.

22:34.353 --> 22:37.356
THIS IS WHERE HE ROAMS...
AND HAUNTS.

22:37.399 --> 22:39.619
SEE, Y'ALL GONNA MAKE ME
GET MY SHOES WET.

22:39.662 --> 22:41.447
THERE'S HIS TOOLBOX.

22:41.490 --> 22:44.537
OOH.

22:44.580 --> 22:47.148
LOOKS LIKE HE'S WORKING
ON THIS THICK, YELLOW HOSE.

22:47.191 --> 22:49.455
WELL, LET'S FOLLOW
THE YELLOW, THICK HOSE.

22:49.498 --> 22:51.195
FOLLOW THE YELLOW,
THICK HOSE.

22:51.239 --> 22:54.677
I SURE HOPE
THERE'S METHANE DOWN HERE,

22:54.721 --> 22:58.333
'CAUSE THE SKINNY ONES
ARE FIRST TO GO.

22:58.377 --> 23:00.596
Chuck: HELLO?

23:00.640 --> 23:02.816
[ WATER DRIPPING ]

23:02.859 --> 23:05.732
HE AIN'T DOWN HERE.
AIN'T NOBODY DOWN HERE.

23:05.775 --> 23:08.952
WE BEEN LOOKING AROUND HERE
FOR HOURS FOLLOWING DEAD GIRL,

23:08.996 --> 23:10.606
AND NOW WE'RE LOST.

23:10.650 --> 23:13.479
WE'RE NOT LOST. WE'RE FOLLOWING
THE YELLOW, THICK HOSE.

23:13.522 --> 23:15.045
WHAT ABOUT
ALL THOSE RUMORS --

23:15.089 --> 23:16.830
THE ONES ABOUT OSCAR ENDING UP
IN A MENTAL INSTITUTION

23:16.873 --> 23:19.485
OR, WORSE YET, BECOMING
A MODERN-DAY MONSTER?

23:19.528 --> 23:21.835
THERE ARE NO SUCH THING
AS MONSTERS.

23:21.878 --> 23:23.097
WHAT ABOUT CHUD?

23:23.140 --> 23:24.490
"CHUD"?

23:24.533 --> 23:27.623
CANNIBALISTIC HUMANOID
UNDERGROUND DWELLERS.

23:27.667 --> 23:31.018
[ Whispering ]
They feed on the homeless
and hapless passersby.

23:31.061 --> 23:32.715
I HEAR
THEY'RE PACK HUNTERS.

23:32.759 --> 23:34.369
YEAH, WELL,
IN THAT CASE,

23:34.413 --> 23:36.327
I SURE HOPE
THEY LIKE WHITE MEAT.

23:36.371 --> 23:37.981
OH, THANKS.

23:38.025 --> 23:39.983
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHERE ARE WE, EXACTLY?

23:40.027 --> 23:44.901
UM...WE SHOULD BE
IN LeNEZ'S NEIGHBORHOOD.

23:47.948 --> 23:49.863
IN FACT...

23:49.906 --> 23:52.561
WE'RE RIGHT UNDERNEATH
HIS APARTMENT BUILDING.

23:54.563 --> 23:57.131
WHAT IS THAT?

24:00.439 --> 24:02.832
WHAT THE HELL IS THAT?

24:04.268 --> 24:06.009
EH!

24:06.053 --> 24:07.750
OSC--
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

24:07.794 --> 24:10.971
OSCAR VIBENIUS?

24:11.014 --> 24:12.320
YOU BETTER RUN!

24:12.363 --> 24:14.801
[ ALL SCREAMING ]

24:22.112 --> 24:22.939
[ CLICKS ]

24:31.861 --> 24:33.689
[ ALARM BEEPING, COUGHS ]

24:39.652 --> 24:41.262
DEPARTMENT OF WATER AND POWER
EMPLOYEE OSCAR VIBENIUS

24:41.305 --> 24:42.785
IS WANTED FOR QUESTIONING

24:42.829 --> 24:45.092
IN THE ATTEMPTED MURDER
OF NAPOLEON LeNEZ,

24:45.135 --> 24:48.922
AUTHOR OF UPCOMING SELF-HELP
OPUS "SMELL OF SUCCESS."

24:48.965 --> 24:51.359
PRESALES OF THE BOOK
HAVE SKYROCKETED

24:51.402 --> 24:52.839
SINCE THE FIRST EXPLOSION,

24:52.882 --> 24:54.971
WHICH CAUSED THE DEATH
OF ANITA GRAY,

24:55.015 --> 24:56.930
A FORMER ASSOCIATE
OF MR. LeNEZ.

24:56.973 --> 24:59.889
I MAY BE CLEAN,
BUT MY MIND IS IN THE GUTTER.

24:59.933 --> 25:02.501
MM, WHAT? DIRTY THOUGHTS?
LASCIVIOUS PININGS?

25:02.544 --> 25:05.460
IN THE SEWER GUTTER
WITH OSCAR VIBENIUS.OH, THAT GUTTER.

25:05.504 --> 25:07.331
HE'S NOT
A VERY GOOD KILLER.

25:07.375 --> 25:09.595
HE KEEPS BLOWING THINGS UP, BUT
NEVER WHO HE WANTSTO BLOW UP.

25:09.638 --> 25:11.597
YEAH, HE'S CERTAINLY
NO SHARPSHOOTER.

25:11.640 --> 25:13.424
MAYBE HE JUST LIKES
THE ATTENTION.

25:13.468 --> 25:14.991
MM-HMM,
I BET HE'S REAL PISSY

25:15.035 --> 25:16.776
THAT NAPOLEON LeNEZ
IS GETTING ALL THE ATTENTION.

25:16.819 --> 25:18.734
OSCAR'S ABOUT TO GET
ALL THE ATTENTION HE WANTS.

25:18.778 --> 25:22.085
OH, UM, SORRY. I DIDN'T KNOW
THAT YOU WERE HERE.

25:22.129 --> 25:24.566
HOW'D YOU GET CLEANED UP
SO QUICK?

25:24.610 --> 25:27.569
I GOT CLEANED UP IN EXACTLY
THE AMOUNT OF TIME IT TAKES
TO GET CLEANED UP.

25:27.613 --> 25:28.962
YOU'RE JUST SLOW.

25:29.005 --> 25:31.704
SO, WHY'S OSCAR GETTING
ALL THE ATTENTION?

25:31.747 --> 25:33.314
LeNEZ'S ABOUT
TO MAKE A STATEMENT,

25:33.357 --> 25:36.099
AND AS WITNESSES TO THE MOST
RECENT ATTEMPT ON HIS LIFE,

25:36.143 --> 25:37.884
WE ALSO HAVE TO MAKE
A STATEMENT,

25:37.927 --> 25:40.060
AND THAT "WE"
DON'T INCLUDE YOU.

25:40.103 --> 25:41.801
WHY NOT? I WITNESSED
THE LATEST ATTEMPT.

25:41.844 --> 25:43.542
THAT DON'T CHANGE THE FACT

25:43.585 --> 25:45.587
THAT THERE'S A GRAVE OUT THERE
THAT YOU SUPPOSED TO BE IN.

25:45.631 --> 25:47.458
WHAT YOU GONNA TELL PEOPLE
WHEN THEY ASK WHO YOU ARE?

25:47.502 --> 25:49.765
I'LL SAY
THAT I'M SOMEBODY I'M NOT.

25:49.809 --> 25:51.985
OH. "HEY, SOMEBODY,
CAN I SEE SOME I.D.?"

25:52.028 --> 25:54.335
WELL, I'LL SMILE,
AND I'LL BE POLITE,

25:54.378 --> 25:56.076
AND I'LL SAY,
"OH, I'M SORRY.

25:56.119 --> 25:58.078
I FORGOT MY PURSE,
AND I'VE GOT NO POCKETS."

25:58.121 --> 25:59.514
UH-HUH.
"WELL, HEY, SOMEBODY,

25:59.558 --> 26:01.255
"SEE, NOW I'M GONNA NEED
TO SEE SOME I.D.

26:01.298 --> 26:03.170
"ON ACCOUNT OF YOU LOOK
JUST LIKE THAT DEAD GIRL

26:03.213 --> 26:05.172
THAT GOT HERSELF KILLED
ON THAT TROPICAL CRUISE."

26:05.215 --> 26:07.566
OKAY, IF THAT HAPPENS,
I'LL SAYING SOMETHING LIKE,

26:07.609 --> 26:09.698
"WHAT IS THIS,
A POLICE STATE?"

26:10.917 --> 26:13.528
IF I EVER SAY THAT, IT MEANS
I'M HAVING A PANIC ATTACK.

26:13.572 --> 26:15.356
NO NEED TO PANIC
'CAUSE SHE AIN'T GOING.

26:15.399 --> 26:16.792
AW.

26:16.836 --> 26:18.011
YOU AIN'T GOING.

26:25.061 --> 26:26.759
[ RHYTHMIC KNOCKING ]

26:30.719 --> 26:34.157
JUST WANTED TO...TRY IT ON
BEFORE I GAVE IT BACK.

26:34.201 --> 26:36.812
WHILE I HAVE YOU HERE,
WOULD YOU TAKE MY PHOTO?

26:36.856 --> 26:38.379
YEAH, SURE.

26:38.422 --> 26:40.642
YOU SHOULD KNOW
THAT OPERATION FIN FOLLIES

26:40.686 --> 26:42.644
IS UP AND FLAPPING.

26:42.688 --> 26:44.472
THE MERMAIDS ARE SINGING.

26:44.515 --> 26:45.821
BUT ARE THEY SWIMMING?

26:45.865 --> 26:47.388
WELL, THEY'RE THINKING
ABOUT SWIMMING,

26:47.431 --> 26:48.694
BUT THEIR HEARTS
ARE SINGING.

26:48.737 --> 26:50.130
AT LEAST
ONE OF THEIR HEARTS.

26:50.173 --> 26:51.392
THE OTHER ONE'S STALLING.

26:51.435 --> 26:53.699
PSYCHOLOGICALLY,
NOT CARDIOLOGICALLY.

26:53.742 --> 26:55.701
LILY.
THAT'S THE ONE.

26:55.744 --> 26:57.877
MAN, HER NUT DON'T CRACK.

26:57.920 --> 27:00.662
LET'S DO ONE
FOR 4th OF JULY.

27:00.706 --> 27:03.056
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:03.099 --> 27:06.363
HER NUT DOESCRACK.
I KNOW IT DOES.

27:06.407 --> 27:08.235
I CRACKED IT BEFORE.

27:08.278 --> 27:10.498
YEAH,
I'VE SEEN THAT CRACK.

27:14.067 --> 27:16.330
THOUGHT MAYBE
YOU'D WANT THIS.

27:19.159 --> 27:21.074
MY AUNTS GAVE IT TO YOU?

27:21.117 --> 27:22.815
PRACTICALLY
FORCED IT ON ME.

27:22.858 --> 27:25.426
I THINK IT'S A BIG FIRST STEP
FOR THEM, EMOTIONALLY.

27:25.469 --> 27:27.167
WHAT ARE THE STAGES OF DEATH?

27:27.210 --> 27:29.648
SOMETHING, SOMETHING, SOMETHING,
SOMETHING, ACCEPTANCE.

27:29.691 --> 27:32.128
[ Voice breaking ] YEAH, UM...
THOSE ARE THE STAGES.

27:32.172 --> 27:33.521
NO, NO.

27:33.564 --> 27:35.610
WE'RE NOT AT THAT STAGE
OF OUR FRIENDSHIP YET.

27:35.654 --> 27:37.220
PLEASE DON'T CRY
IN FRONT OF ME.

27:37.264 --> 27:39.875
DON'T DO IT.
DON'T YOU DO IT!I'M NOT GOING TO.

27:39.919 --> 27:41.094
YOU BETTER NOT.

27:41.137 --> 27:43.096
[ High-pitched voice ]
I WON'T.

27:43.139 --> 27:44.619
[ SOBBING ]

27:44.663 --> 27:46.577
YOU DID IT.

27:46.621 --> 27:49.580
UM...

27:49.624 --> 27:52.148
WOULD YOU LIKE
A PIECE OF PIE?

27:53.933 --> 27:56.109
Woman:
WHAT CAN SMELL DO FOR YOU?

27:56.152 --> 27:59.634
IF YOU'RE NAPOLEON LeNEZ,
AUTHOR OF "SMELL OF SUCCESS,"

27:59.678 --> 28:04.726
THE CONTROVERSIAL NEW GUIDE TO
SATISFACTION THROUGH OLFACTION,

28:04.770 --> 28:07.163
SMELL CAN GET YOU KILLED.

28:07.207 --> 28:10.950
NAPOLEON, HOW MANY ATTEMPTS
HAVE THERE BEEN ON YOUR LIFE?

28:10.993 --> 28:13.779
RIGHT NOW,
THERE'S ONLY BEEN TWO, CAROL.

28:13.822 --> 28:16.564
AND YOU'RE
ANTICIPATING MORE?I DON'T KNOW.

28:16.607 --> 28:17.913
SEEMS LIKE
SOMEBODY OUT THERE

28:17.957 --> 28:19.523
DOESN'T WANT MY BOOK
TOUCHING THE WORLD.

28:19.567 --> 28:21.743
SIMPLY PURGING YOUR LIFE
OF THE BAD SMELLS

28:21.787 --> 28:23.223
AND FOCUSING ON THE GOOD.

28:23.266 --> 28:25.529
IT'S ALL THERE IN MY BOOK,
"SMELL OF SUCCESS."

28:25.573 --> 28:27.183
BUT IT'S NOT JUST SOMEBODY.

28:27.227 --> 28:30.317
YOU KNOW THE MAN WHO MADE
TWO ATTEMPTS ON YOUR LIFE.

28:30.360 --> 28:31.448
YES, I DO.

28:31.492 --> 28:34.147
HIS NAME
IS OSCAR VIBENIUS.

28:34.190 --> 28:37.585
HERE WITH US NOW
IS AN EYEWITNESS

28:37.628 --> 28:41.241
TO OSCAR VIBENIUS' ATTEMPT
ON YOUR LIFE EARLIER TODAY.

28:41.284 --> 28:43.069
SIR,
TELL US WHAT YOU SAW.

28:43.112 --> 28:44.287
GOOD EVENING, CAROL.

28:44.331 --> 28:45.680
LET ME PREFACE MY STATEMENT

28:45.724 --> 28:47.682
BY SAYING THAT MY NAME
IS EMERSON COD.

28:47.726 --> 28:48.857
I'M A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR.

28:48.901 --> 28:50.293
IF YOU NEED TO REACH ME,

28:50.337 --> 28:52.731
MY TELEPHONE NUMBER
IS KLONDIKE 5-0155.

28:52.774 --> 28:55.385
THAT'S KLONDIKE 5-0155.

28:55.429 --> 28:57.779
I'VE BEEN INVESTIGATING
THE ANITA GRAY MURDER.

28:57.823 --> 28:59.520
SHE WAS TAKEN
MUCH TOO SOON.

28:59.563 --> 29:02.392
GET A LOAD
OF MUGGY McHAMBONE.HAWKING HIS WARES.

29:02.436 --> 29:05.134
HE JUST GAVE OUT HIS PHONE
NUMBER ON NATIONAL TELEVISION.

29:05.178 --> 29:06.701
LOOK.
THERE'S THE KILLER.

29:06.745 --> 29:08.703
[ DOOR OPENS, BELL DINGS ]

29:08.747 --> 29:11.532
WHAT MAKES SOMEBODY
LIKE OSCAR VIBENIUS DO IT?

29:11.575 --> 29:13.795
LOOK.
THERE'S THE KILLER.

29:13.839 --> 29:15.841
OH, LORD.

29:21.455 --> 29:23.413
DON'T MAKE ME
CUT A BITCH.

29:23.457 --> 29:26.373
HEY, I'M JUST HERE
FOR PIE AND CONVERSATION,

29:26.416 --> 29:28.941
NEITHER OF WHICH ARE CAUSE
TO CALL A MAN A BITCH.

29:28.984 --> 29:31.247
YOU'RE TRYING
TO KILL NAPOLEON LeNEZ.

29:31.291 --> 29:33.467
IF I AM,
I'M NOT A VERY GOOD KILLER.

29:33.510 --> 29:36.731
I KEEP BLOWING THINGS UP,
BUT NEVER WHO I WANT TO BLOW UP?

29:36.775 --> 29:39.690
I SAID THAT.
HAVE YOU BEEN SPYING ON ME?

29:39.734 --> 29:41.736
YOU'D BE SURPRISED
WHAT YOU CAN HEAR

29:41.780 --> 29:43.216
WHEN YOU PRESS YOUR EAR
TO THE RIGHT PIPE.

29:43.259 --> 29:46.088
IF IT WASN'T YOU, THEN
WHO WAS TRYING TO KILL LeNEZ?

29:46.132 --> 29:47.568
I HAVE THEORIES.

29:47.611 --> 29:49.309
YOU'VE BEEN CONDUCTING
YOUR INVESTIGATION.

29:49.352 --> 29:51.137
I'VE BEEN CONDUCTING MINE.

29:51.180 --> 29:54.140
WE SHOULD TALK, COMPARE NOTES,
COME TO CONCLUSIONS.

29:54.183 --> 29:56.142
NOW, HOW'S ABOUT YOU PUT
THAT KNIFE TO USE

29:56.185 --> 29:58.971
AND CUT ME OFF
A PIECE OF PERSIMMON PIE?

29:59.014 --> 30:00.624
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S COMPARE NOTES.

30:00.668 --> 30:03.149
WHY WERE YOU IN THE SEWER WITH
YOUR HANDS ON A BOOBY TRAP?

30:03.192 --> 30:05.020
Narrator:
WHY OSCAR VIBENIUS

30:05.064 --> 30:07.849
HAD HIS HANDS
ON A BOOBY TRAP WAS THIS.

30:07.893 --> 30:10.809
AFTER LEARNING OF THE ATTEMPT
ON LeNEZ'S LIFE,

30:10.852 --> 30:14.377
MR. VIBENIUS TRAILED HIS FORMER
COLLEAGUE TO A SEWER MAIN,

30:14.421 --> 30:16.684
WHERE HE LOST TRACK OF HIM.

30:16.727 --> 30:18.860
BUT WHAT HE FOUND IN HIS STEAD

30:18.904 --> 30:21.645
WAS A MYSTERIOUS
YELLOW, THICK HOSE,

30:21.689 --> 30:23.517
[ SNIFFING ]WHICH HE QUICKLY REALIZED

30:23.560 --> 30:27.521
WAS PART OF A PLOT TO BLOW UP
NAPOLEON LeNEZ'S CAR.

30:27.564 --> 30:29.653
HE WORKED QUICKLY
TO DISABLE THE THREAT,

30:29.697 --> 30:31.873
BUT COULDN'T DISMANTLE THE BOMB

30:31.917 --> 30:34.310
BEFORE HE WAS STARTLED
IN THE DARK.

30:34.354 --> 30:36.269
[ ALL SCREAMING ]

30:36.312 --> 30:38.924
Narrator: FEARING SAID BOMB
WAS ABOUT TO BLOW,

30:38.967 --> 30:42.188
HE CHOSE TO RUN FOR COVER RATHER
THAN EXPLAIN HIS ACTIONS.

30:42.231 --> 30:43.885
HOW DO WE KNOW
YOU'RE TELLING THE TRUTH?

30:43.929 --> 30:46.235
LeNEZ PRACTICALLY SAID
THAT YOU WERE A CHUD --

30:46.279 --> 30:48.716
A CANNIBALISTIC --I KNOW WHAT A CHUD IS,
AND I KNOW NAPOLEON LeNEZ.

30:48.759 --> 30:51.371
DID HE TELL YOU WHAT YOU SMELLED
LIKE WHEN YOU MET HIM?

30:51.414 --> 30:52.720
HE THINKS PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

30:52.763 --> 30:54.853
HE SAID
I SMELLED LIKE HONEY.

30:54.896 --> 30:57.464
LIKE YOU'VE BEEN DIPPED
IN IT.

30:57.507 --> 31:00.032
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

31:00.075 --> 31:02.730
THERE'S SOMETHING ELSE
YOU SMELL LIKE.

31:02.773 --> 31:06.299
I KNOW. DEATH.
IT'S MY PERFUME.

31:06.342 --> 31:08.040
YOU'RE NOT WEARING PERFUME.

31:08.083 --> 31:10.564
NO, THIS ISN'T DEATH.

31:10.607 --> 31:12.696
THIS IS SOMETHING ELSE
ALTOGETHER.

31:12.740 --> 31:15.221
[ SNIFFING ]

31:15.264 --> 31:17.745
I'VE NEVER SMELLED
ANYTHING LIKE IT.

31:17.788 --> 31:20.052
DO ME. DO ME.
WHAT DO I SMELL LIKE?

31:20.095 --> 31:21.270
DOG.

31:21.314 --> 31:22.881
NEVER MIND DOG.
WE NEED PROOF.

31:22.924 --> 31:24.491
WE'RE NOT GONNA BELIEVE YOU
JUST BECAUSE YOU SAY SO.

31:24.534 --> 31:26.406
WOULD YOU BELIEVE
YOUR NOSES?

31:27.624 --> 31:29.800
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
SMELLS LIKE ROTTEN EGGS.

31:29.844 --> 31:31.019
WELL,
IT WAS INCINERATED

31:31.063 --> 31:32.586
IN AN EXPLODING BALL
OF METHANE GAS.

31:32.629 --> 31:33.935
WHAT ELSE
WOULD IT SMELL LIKE?

31:33.979 --> 31:36.677
NOTHING.
OH.

31:36.720 --> 31:38.070
METHANE GAS IS ODORLESS.

31:38.113 --> 31:40.072
I COOK WITH GAS.
IT SMELLS LIKE ROTTEN EGGS.

31:40.115 --> 31:41.769
THE UTILITY COMPANIES ADD
A SYNTHETIC CHEMICAL SMELL TO IT

31:41.812 --> 31:43.466
BEFORE IT'S PUMPED
INTO OUR HOUSES.

31:43.510 --> 31:45.860
BUT A METHANE EXPLOSION IN
THE SEWER WOULDN'T HAVE A SMELL,

31:45.904 --> 31:49.037
UNLESS SOMEONE THOUGHT AN
IGNORANT PUBLIC EXPECTED IT TO.

31:49.081 --> 31:51.431
SOMEONE ELITIST,

31:51.474 --> 31:54.173
SOMEONE LIKE LeNEZ.

31:54.216 --> 31:55.826
AND WITH A BOOK
ABOUT TO BE PUBLISHED,

31:55.870 --> 31:57.828
HE HAS THE MOST TO GAIN
BY AN ATTEMPT ON HIS LIFE.

31:57.872 --> 32:01.223
NOTHING SELLS BOOKS LIKE
A LITTLE MURDER AND MAYHEM.

32:01.267 --> 32:03.617
I ALREADY
PREORDERED MY COPY.

32:03.660 --> 32:07.664
Narrator: AS NAPOLEON LeNEZ'S
STAR APPEARED TO RISE,

32:07.708 --> 32:10.406
LILY AND VIVIAN'S STAR
CONTINUED TO FALL

32:10.450 --> 32:12.017
AS THEY MADE THEIR WAY

32:12.060 --> 32:15.194
THROUGH A BOX OF SLIDES
DOCUMENTING HAPPIER TIMES.

32:15.237 --> 32:16.717
OH, LOOK, LILY!

32:16.760 --> 32:20.155
IT'S WHEN WE WENT
TO THE HEBREW FETA SECT.

32:22.941 --> 32:25.160
[ SIGHS ]
I MISS MY EYE.

32:25.204 --> 32:26.945
PECULIAR.

32:26.988 --> 32:28.729
WHAT?

32:28.772 --> 32:30.644
YOU SAID YOU MISS
YOUR EYE BEFORE YOU
SAID YOU MISS CHARLOTTE.

32:30.687 --> 32:32.515
WHEN I LOOKED
AT THAT PICTURE,

32:32.559 --> 32:34.387
THE FIRST THING
I THOUGHT OF WAS,
"I MISS CHARLOTTE."

32:34.430 --> 32:36.432
GOOD GOD, VIVIAN.

32:36.476 --> 32:39.305
IT WAS THE FIRST THING
I THOUGHT OF, TOO.

32:39.348 --> 32:43.135
IT JUST SO HAPPENS, I DON'T
ALWAYS SAY EVERYTHING I THINK.

32:43.178 --> 32:44.875
FANCY THAT.

32:48.009 --> 32:51.056
IT WASN'T YOUR EYE --
WHY WE STOPPED SWIMMING.

32:51.099 --> 32:54.015
WE TOLD PEOPLE IT WAS,
BUT IT WASN'T.

32:54.059 --> 32:56.670
WE'VE BEEN STOPPED SWIMMING
LONG ENOUGH

32:56.713 --> 32:59.586
FOR IT NOT TO MATTER
WHY WE STOPPED SWIMMING.

32:59.629 --> 33:03.720
IT USED TO MAKE YOU SO HAPPY,
THE WATER.

33:03.764 --> 33:07.637
I THINK IT'S BRAVE
TO TRY TO BE HAPPY.

33:07.681 --> 33:11.337
YOU'VE GOTTEN SO COMFORTABLE
BEING UNHAPPY.

33:11.380 --> 33:13.382
WOULDN'T IT BE WONDERFUL

33:13.426 --> 33:17.604
TO WAKE UP IN THE MORNING
AND CHOOSE TO BE HAPPY,

33:17.647 --> 33:20.999
TO LET THE WATER WASH
EVERYTHING AWAY?

33:24.176 --> 33:26.178
[ SCOFFS ]

33:34.838 --> 33:38.059
YOU FORGOT
YOUR CHLORINE TABLETS.

33:38.103 --> 33:40.931
Narrator:
HER OLFACTORY GLANDS STIMULATED

33:40.975 --> 33:43.847
WITH THE SMELLS
OF SYNCHRONIZED SWIMMING,

33:43.891 --> 33:46.546
LILY EXPERIENCED
A FLOOD OF ENDORPHINS

33:46.589 --> 33:49.375
FROM THE SCENT
OF BOTTLED SUNSHINE

33:49.418 --> 33:53.161
AS NAPOLEON LeNEZ EXPERIENCED
A FLOOD OF ENDORPHINS

33:53.205 --> 33:54.771
FROM HIS MEDIA BLITZ,

33:54.815 --> 33:56.251
WHICH LEFT THE PIE MAKER

33:56.295 --> 33:58.297
TO CARRY OUT A BLIND-SIDE BLITZ
OF HIS OWN.

33:58.340 --> 33:59.559
[ Coughing ]
EMERSON!

33:59.602 --> 34:01.343
WHERE DID YOU GO?

34:01.387 --> 34:02.518
I WAS
BORED AND SNOOPING.

34:02.562 --> 34:04.390
OKAY, MAYBE
IPSO FACTO SNOOPING,

34:04.433 --> 34:06.827
BUT IT WASN'T
MY GOAL TO SNOOP,
JUST ENTERTAIN MYSELF.

34:06.870 --> 34:08.829
YOU KNOW HOW
WHEN YOU'RE A GUEST
AND YOU'RE BORED

34:08.872 --> 34:10.178
AND YOU GO INTO
THE BATHROOM AND READ
THROUGH THE MAGAZINES

34:10.222 --> 34:11.571
AND RUMMAGE THROUGH
THE MEDICINE CABINET,

34:11.614 --> 34:13.094
LOOK IN THE CLOSETS
AND UNDER THE BED,

34:13.138 --> 34:14.617
AND YOU FIND SOMETHING
YOU WERE NEVER MEANT TO SEE?

34:14.661 --> 34:17.446
GET TO THE POINT.

34:17.490 --> 34:19.100
DAMN.

34:19.144 --> 34:23.061
WELL...THAT COULDN'T HAVE GONE
BETTER IF I'D PLANNED IT.

34:23.104 --> 34:25.367
SMELL IT,
CRAVE IT, OWN IT.

34:25.411 --> 34:26.716
THAT'S THE SPIRIT.

34:26.760 --> 34:28.936
SO, ONCE YOU SMELL IT,
THEN YOU CRAVE IT.

34:28.979 --> 34:31.417
HOW FAR ARE YOU WILLING TO GO
BEFORE YOU OWN IT?HMM.

34:31.460 --> 34:34.376
YOU CAN'T JUST SCRATCH
AND SNIFF AND MAKE A WISH.

34:34.420 --> 34:36.248
YOU GOT TO HAVE A PLAN,
AND ACCORDING TO YOU,

34:36.291 --> 34:37.901
THIS THING COULDN'T
HAVE GONE BETTER

34:37.945 --> 34:40.165
IF YOU'D PLANNED IT YOURSELF,
WHICH LEADS ME TO BELIEVE --

34:40.208 --> 34:42.080
YOU PLANNED IT YOURSELF.

34:42.123 --> 34:44.212
YOU SET OSCAR UP

34:44.256 --> 34:47.259
AFTER YOU FIGURED OUT
THE CORRECT SPACING.

34:47.302 --> 34:51.393
THIS IS RIDIC--
HOW DARE --

34:51.437 --> 34:52.916
YOU PLANTED THAT SOCK.

34:52.960 --> 34:56.746
I AM NOT GOING TO STAND HERE
AND BE ACCUSED.

34:56.790 --> 34:58.444
I THINK IT'S BEST
IF YOU BOTH LEAVE.

34:58.487 --> 35:00.010
I CONCUR.

35:01.838 --> 35:03.188
[ DOOR OPENS ]

35:03.231 --> 35:06.104
[ CLICKING ]

35:06.147 --> 35:07.366
OH!

35:07.409 --> 35:08.584
Napoleon:
WHEN I SUGGESTED YOU LEAVE,

35:08.628 --> 35:10.369
I DIDN'T MEAN THE PENTHOUSE.

35:10.412 --> 35:12.371
I MEANT THIS MORTAL COIL.

35:12.414 --> 35:14.677
CONGRATULATIONS, GENTLEMEN.

35:14.721 --> 35:16.157
YOU'RE ABOUT TO FALL VICTIM

35:16.201 --> 35:17.637
TO ATTEMPT NUMBER THREE
ON MY LIFE.

35:17.680 --> 35:19.465
[ ALARM BEEPING ]BUT DON'T WORRY.

35:19.508 --> 35:21.075
I'LL MENTION YOU
IN THE ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS

35:21.119 --> 35:22.729
OF THE SECOND PRINTING
OF MY BOOK.

35:25.558 --> 35:27.951
OH, HELL, NO!

35:33.305 --> 35:34.958
AAH![ BANGING ]

35:35.002 --> 35:36.395
HEY!

35:36.438 --> 35:39.528
YOU GOT EXACTLY 3 SECONDS
TO OPEN THIS DAMN DOOR!

35:39.572 --> 35:41.617
WAIT. [ SNIFFS ]
WHAT'S THAT --

35:41.661 --> 35:43.489
THAT SMELL IS
THE CHAMBER FILLING UP

35:43.532 --> 35:45.447
WITH AN AMALGAMATION
OF EXPLOSIVE GASES,

35:45.491 --> 35:46.927
WHICH WILL ERUPT ON MY MARK.

35:46.970 --> 35:49.190
SO, PLEASE,
IF YOU'RE IN A HURRY TO DIE,

35:49.234 --> 35:51.932
FIRE YOUR GUN
AND SET THE CHAMBER ABLAZE.

35:51.975 --> 35:53.542
BUT KILLING US ISN'T GONNA
CHANGE ANYTHING!

35:53.586 --> 35:55.196
SAYS YOU.

35:55.240 --> 35:58.112
IMAGINE THE PUBLIC OUTCRY
WHEN THE PRESS RELEASES PHOTOS

35:58.156 --> 36:00.288
OF MY CHARRED
DECONTAMINATION CHAMBER,

36:00.332 --> 36:02.812
THE CRISPY CORPSES
OF TWO PRIVATE DETECTIVES

36:02.856 --> 36:04.205
UNFORTUNATE ENOUGH TO TRIGGER

36:04.249 --> 36:06.816
MY NEMESIS'S THIRD ATTEMPT
ON MY LIFE.

36:06.860 --> 36:09.210
HOW TRAGIC,
BUT HOW PERFECTLY TITILLATING.

36:09.254 --> 36:12.170
BOY, ANITA SURE MADE
A BIG MISTAKE

36:12.213 --> 36:13.649
HITCHING HER HORSE
TO YOUR WAGON.

36:13.693 --> 36:16.652
DON'T SAY THAT.
I NEVER MEANT TO HURT HER.

36:16.696 --> 36:18.480
YOU KILLED HER!

36:18.524 --> 36:20.134
BUT I DIDN'T MEANTO.

36:20.178 --> 36:23.355
HER DEATH WAS AN ACCIDENT.

36:23.398 --> 36:24.791
Narrator:
WHEN IT BECAME CLEAR

36:24.834 --> 36:27.228
HIS PUBLISHER WAS GOING
TO BURY HIS LIFE'S WORK,

36:27.272 --> 36:30.536
LeNEZ CONCOCTED AN EXPLOSIVE
MARKETING STRATEGY

36:30.579 --> 36:32.015
OF HIS VERY OWN.

36:32.059 --> 36:34.322
HE WOULD BOOST INTEREST
IN HIS BOOK

36:34.366 --> 36:38.065
BY PRETENDING TO BE THE TARGET
OF A MURDEROUS RIVAL'S ATTACK.

36:38.108 --> 36:40.633
HIS DISCOVERY
OF THE BOOBY-TRAPPED TOME

36:40.676 --> 36:42.939
WOULD CREATE
A PUBLICITY WHIRLWIND

36:42.983 --> 36:44.898
HIS PUBLISHER COULD NOT IGNORE.

36:44.941 --> 36:47.901
BUT THERE WERE VARIABLES
HE COULDN'T CONTROL,

36:47.944 --> 36:49.729
INCLUDING THE UTTER DEVOTION

36:49.772 --> 36:53.385
OF HIS MOST DEDICATED STUDENT,
ANITA GRAY,

36:53.428 --> 36:55.909
WHO COULDN'T RESIST
A QUICK SNIFF.

36:55.952 --> 36:57.563
[ SNIFFS, EXPLOSION ]

36:57.606 --> 37:00.130
Narrator: STILL, ANITA'S DEATH
ONLY FUELED THE FIRE,

37:00.174 --> 37:02.263
INCREASING HIS BOOK'S PRESALES
EXPONENTIALLY.

37:02.307 --> 37:04.134
SO, WITHOUT FURTHER ADO,

37:04.178 --> 37:07.268
[ DOOR BANGS ]LeNEZ SET THE REST
OF HIS PLOT IN MOTION.

37:07.312 --> 37:09.575
HE PINNED THE CRIME ON OSCAR,
AS PLANNED,

37:09.618 --> 37:12.273
AND FURTHER CAPITALIZED
ON THE GROWING PUBLICITY

37:12.317 --> 37:17.409
BY STAGING A SECOND, MORE
SPECTACULAR ATTEMPT ON HIS LIFE,

37:17.452 --> 37:21.674
AN ATTEMPT THAT OSCAR HIMSELF
MISTAKENLY HELPED LEGITIMIZE

37:21.717 --> 37:24.285
BY APPEARING ON THE SCENE
TO STOP IT.

37:24.329 --> 37:25.547
GOODBYE, GENTLEMEN.

37:25.591 --> 37:27.854
PLEASE GIVE ANITA
MY FELICITATIONS.

37:27.897 --> 37:30.857
AND, AGAIN, TELL HER I'M SORRY.

37:30.900 --> 37:32.424
[ CLICKING ]

37:32.467 --> 37:34.513
[ ELEVATOR DINGS ]

37:35.905 --> 37:37.342
NED!CHUCK!

37:37.385 --> 37:40.388
OSCAR!NAPOLEON!

37:40.432 --> 37:42.260
HI, EMERSON.

37:42.303 --> 37:43.565
HEY, OLIVE.

37:43.609 --> 37:45.306
Ned: WAIT, NO, NO!

37:45.350 --> 37:48.222
IT'S OKAY!
OSCAR REVERSED THE PUMPS!

37:48.266 --> 37:49.441
HE WHAT?

37:49.484 --> 37:51.312
Narrator:
USING HIS EXPERT KNOWLEDGE

37:51.356 --> 37:53.488
OF THE CITY'S UNDERGROUND
ELECTRICAL GRID,

37:53.532 --> 37:57.753
OSCAR HAD REPROGRAMMED LeNEZ'S
ENTIRE DECONTAMINATION SYSTEM

37:57.797 --> 38:00.452
JUST PRIOR
TO ENTERING THE BUILDING.

38:00.495 --> 38:03.063
REPURPOSED AND REJIGGERED,

38:03.106 --> 38:06.284
[ CLICKING ]IT NO LONGER PROTECTED HIM
FROM THE OUTSIDE WORLD.

38:06.327 --> 38:09.112
INSTEAD, IT DID
JUST THE OPPOSITE.

38:09.156 --> 38:12.159
NO. NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

38:12.202 --> 38:15.162
NO. NO!

38:15.205 --> 38:18.252
[ COUGHING ]
NO!!

38:19.862 --> 38:21.603
[ WHIMPERING ]

38:26.347 --> 38:27.566
[ THUD ]

38:27.609 --> 38:28.871
[ DOOR OPENS ]

38:28.915 --> 38:31.657
Narrator:
AS THE SYSTEM PURGED ITSELF,

38:31.700 --> 38:35.487
[ MUMBLING ]THE MAN WHO DEMANDED PURITY
WAS BRANDED A FILTHY MURDERER.

38:35.530 --> 38:38.054
AND THE MAN WHO EMBRACED FILTH

38:38.098 --> 38:41.754
REJOICED THAT HIS SOLID
REPUTATION HAD BEEN CLEANSED.

38:41.797 --> 38:45.018
I'M CANCELING
MY PREORDER.

38:45.061 --> 38:48.326
Narrator: SATISFIED THAT
ANOTHER CASE HAD BEEN CLOSED,

38:48.369 --> 38:50.850
OUR HEROES RETURNED HOME.

38:50.893 --> 38:54.244
ELSEWHERE,
A TENTATIVE BREEZE OF HOPE

38:54.288 --> 38:57.204
SIGNALED A NEW BEGINNING.

38:57.247 --> 39:03.863
♪ MORNING HAS BROKEN

39:03.906 --> 39:10.609
♪ LIKE THE FIRST MORNING

39:10.652 --> 39:16.615
♪ BLACKBIRD HAS SPOKEN

39:16.658 --> 39:19.618
♪ LIKE THE FIRST BIRD

39:19.661 --> 39:23.317
[ SCOFFS ]
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

39:23.361 --> 39:29.497
♪ PRAISE FOR THE SINGING

39:29.541 --> 39:34.633
♪ PRAISE FOR THE MORNING

39:34.676 --> 39:40.029
♪ PRAISE FOR THEM SPRINGING

39:40.073 --> 39:47.210
♪ FRESH FROM THE WORD

39:47.254 --> 39:51.389
♪ SWEET THE RAIN'S NEW FALL

39:51.432 --> 39:55.436
♪ SUNLIT FROM HEAVEN

39:55.480 --> 39:59.875
♪ LIKE THE FIRST DEWFALL

39:59.919 --> 40:03.966
♪ ON THE FIRST GRASS

40:04.010 --> 40:08.101
♪ PRAISE FOR THE SWEETNESS

40:08.144 --> 40:12.192
♪ OF THE WET GARDEN

40:12.235 --> 40:16.457
♪ SPRUNG IN COMPLETENESS

40:16.501 --> 40:22.245
♪ WHERE HIS FEET PASSED

40:22.289 --> 40:26.424
♪ MINE IS THE SUNLIGHT

40:26.467 --> 40:30.123
♪ MINE IS THE MORNING

40:30.166 --> 40:34.475
♪ BORN OF THE ONE LIGHT

40:34.519 --> 40:39.175
♪ EDEN SAW PLAY

40:39.219 --> 40:44.137
♪ PRAISE WITH ELATION

40:44.180 --> 40:50.273
♪ PRAISE EVERY MORNING

40:50.317 --> 40:56.497
♪ GOD'S RE-CREATION

40:56.541 --> 41:08.335
♪ OF THE NEW DAY

41:08.378 --> 41:10.337
Narrator:
ANOTHER CASE CLOSED,

41:10.380 --> 41:13.775
EMERSON TEMPORARILY
SET ASIDE HIS KNITTING NEEDLES

41:13.819 --> 41:15.473
TO PURSUE A NEW HOBBY...

41:19.215 --> 41:22.349
...ONE THAT MAGNIFIED
HIS HAPPINESS TENFOLD.

41:22.392 --> 41:25.178
I LOVEPOP-UP BOOKS.

41:31.445 --> 41:34.753
HEY. YOU HAVEN'T SEEN
MY OLD SWEATER, HAVE YOU?

41:34.796 --> 41:38.365
NO. HAVE YOU SEEN
MY NEW MENUS?

41:38.408 --> 41:40.367
NO.

41:40.410 --> 41:42.021
FOR ME?

41:42.064 --> 41:44.327
FOR YOU.

41:48.418 --> 41:51.857
[ SIGHS ]
CUP-PIES.

41:51.900 --> 41:53.815
Narrator:
THE MERE SIGHT OF EACH OTHER

41:53.859 --> 41:56.862
LEFT THE PIE MAKER
AND THE GIRL NAMED CHUCK

41:56.905 --> 41:59.865
FEELING EXACTLY LIKE
THEY WANTED TO FEEL --

41:59.908 --> 42:03.129
SAFE AND WARM AND LOVED.

42:08.526 --> 42:10.919
MEANWHILE, OSCAR VIBENIUS

42:10.963 --> 42:13.922
EMBRACED AN OBSESSION
OF HIS OWN.

42:19.624 --> 42:23.062
CHUCK AND HER SECRET
WERE IN DANGER.

42:23.105 --> 42:26.718
AND THIS TIME, IT WASN'T
SO MUCH ABOUT THE TELLING

42:26.761 --> 42:30.417
AS IT WAS THE SMELLING.
